==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wolverine
<hw>Wol`ver*ine"</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Wolf</er>, with a dim suffix;
prob. so called from its supposed wolfish qualities.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A carnivorous mammal (<spn>Gulo gulo</spn>
formerly <spn>Gulo luscus</spn>), of the weasel family
<fam>Mustelidae</fam>, about the size of a large badger; called also
<altname>glutton</altname> and <altname>carcajou</altname>. It is a
native of the northern parts of America, Europe, and Asia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A nickname for an inhabitant of Michigan.</def>
<mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wolverine State</ent>⟦br⟧
